                " \n \nACCOUNTANT: OPERATIONAL FINANCE\n \nDetails\nClosing Date: 2023/10/06\nReference Number: PRE230928-4\nJob Title: Accountant: Operational Finance\nDepartment: Corporate Finance\nSite: 975 - Premier Corporate\nJob Type Classification: Permanent\nLocation \u2013 Country: South Africa\nLocation - Town / City: Waterfall\nLocation \u2013 Province: Gauteng\n \nJob Description\nWe are a leading FMCG company dedicated to delivering quality products to our customers. We're on the lookout for a skilled Accountant to join our finance team in the Midrand area. If you're passionate about finance and want to contribute to our dynamic FMCG environment, this role is for you.\nAs an Operational Finance Accountant, you will be responsible for managing financial functions within our operations. This role involves ensuring financial controls, accurate record-keeping, and comprehensive reporting to mitigate risks.\n \nKey Responsibilities:\nEnsuring financial integrity, transparency, and compliance by: Initiating and maintaining company procedures and policies related to administration and finance, manage financial risks, and oversee financial month-end activities up to the trial balance. Reviewing and reporting on balance sheet reconciliations. Compiling necessary reports within established deadlines.\nOptimising financial performance and resource allocation by: Checking, consolidating, monitoring budgets, reporting variances, and assist in cost management and waste reduction initiatives.\nFacilitating informed decision-making and strategic planning, by: Conducting forecasting, financial projections, and assisting with capital expenditure (capex) applications and budget reviews.\nSafeguarding company assets, stock, and financial resources, by: Managing assets and stock to prevent theft and financial losses, managing debtors and creditors, and ensuring correctness and accuracy of financial data.\nLeading and supervising the finance team, ensuring compliance with principles, values, and technology, by: Overseeing Human Resources functions, managing the ongoing functionality of IT infrastructure, and preparing and assisting with audits.\n \nQualification Requirements   \nAn essential requirement is a Bachelor's degree in Accounting with a specialisation in Cost & Management Accounting.\n \nExperience Requirements    \nEssential 2-3 years of operational experience in the (FMCG) industry.\nEssential 2-3 years of supervisory experience.\nDesirable 2-3 years of auditing experience.\n \nKey Outputs\n \nRequirements:\nJob Knowledge:\nIntermediate proficiency in ERP systems (e.g., Microsoft Great Plains or equivalent) is highly desirable.\n \nJob-Related Skills:\nAdvanced Excel skills, including pivot tables and formulas, are essential.\nEssential skills in people management, basic industrial relations (IR), and intermediate analytical thinking, planning, and organising.\nProficiency in intermediate-level communication skills is crucial for effective collaboration.\n \n \nPolicy\nPlease note that it is company policy to promote from within wherever possible, hence internal applicants will be given priority. We recruit and appoint in line with our Employment Equity Goals and objectives.\n \nPLEASE APPLY HERE\n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \nDRIVER: SALESMAN\n \nDetails\nClosing Date: 2023/10/04\nReference Number: PRE230927-2\nJob Title: Driver: Salesman\nDepartment: Bakery Sales\nSite: 674 - BRB Mthatha\nJob Type Classification: Permanent\nLocation \u2013 Country: South Africa\nLocation - Town / City: Mthatha\nLocation \u2013 Province: Eastern Cape\n \nJob Description\nTruck stock and cash\nVisiting of customers daily on route\nFinding new business on route to customers\nBalancing of trays on a daily basis\nReconciling at site after route\nBanking of cash\nReturning all POD\u2019s\nPressurised environment\n6-day position\nRequired to work Saturdays, Sundays and Public Holidays as per shift roster\nRequired to work in alternative areas as required by the business\n \nQualification Requirements   \nMatric\nMust have valid Code 10 driver\u2019s license and PrDP\nExperience Requirements      \nA minimum of 24 months driving experience\n2-3 years in a similar role\n \nKey Outputs\nCore business processes and capabilities\nIndustry (FMCG)\nAccuracy / Attention to detail\nDecision making ability/Analytical thinking\nOrganising / Planning\nPhysical ability\nProblem solving\nSupportiveness\nInnovation / Continuous Improvements\nTeamwork\nAccountability\nSense of urgency / results orientation\n \nPolicy\nPlease note that it is company policy to promote from within wherever possible, hence internal applicants will be given priority. We recruit and appoint in line with our Employment Equity Goals and objectives.\n \nPLEASE APPLY HERE\n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \nSALES REPRESENTATIVE\n \nDetails\nClosing Date: 2023/10/04\nReference Number: PRE230927-1\nJob Title: Sales Representative\nDepartment: Sales\nSite: 355 - BRB Aeroton\nJob Type Classification: Permanent\nLocation \u2013 Country: South Africa\nLocation - Town / City: Springs\nLocation \u2013 Province: Gauteng\n \nJob Description\nMain Objectives\nResponsible for maintaining and growing existing targets across client base in the Informal trade. \n \nKey Responsibilities\nFloor walk, Stock management and presentation\nReturns, Administration\nOrders, New business accounts\nSales growth (by category)\nCommunication and interdepartmental synergy, Sales targets\nCrate Control, Cold Calling, Buildings Displays\nRelationship building internal and external customers, Route Riding\n \nQualification Requirements   \nExperience and Qualifications\nMatric & 3-5 years sales experience\n \nExperience Requirements    \nExperience:\n3-5 years sales experience in an FMCG environment.\n \nKey Outputs   \nCompetencies, Knowledge (Job Related Skills)\nBusiness procedures, rules and processes\nCompetition / competitor activity\nClient / Consumer relationships\nOrganisational understanding, Sales Processes, Analytical thinking\nAccuracy / attention to detail, Communication, Decision making\nAssertiveness, Conflict handling & Influencing / negotiating\nProactivity, Interpersonal skills\nInnovation / continuous improvement\nTeamwork, Accountability\nSense of urgency, Respect & IR\n \nOther Requirements\nNeed to balance office and trade\nRelationship building is imperative\nFlexibility in terms of relevant client location\nCode 08 license\nField Marketer\nMerchandising experience\nRequired to work Saturdays, Sundays and Public Holidays\n \n \nPolicy\nPlease note that it is company policy to promote from within wherever possible, hence internal applicants will be given priority. We recruit and appoint in line with our Employment Equity Goals and objectives.\n \nPLEASE APPLY HERE\n \n \n \n ",
                "OPERATIONS CLERK: TEMP\n \nDetails\nClosing Date: 2023/10/02\nReference Number: PRE230926-1\nJob Title: Operations Clerk: Temp\nDepartment: Maintenance\nSite: 611 - Premier East London Mill\nJob Type Classification: Fixed Term Contract\nLocation \u2013 Country: South Africa\nLocation - Town / City: East London\nLocation \u2013 Province: Eastern Cape\n \nJob Description\nPurpose of the job:\nExecute the Planned preventive Maintenance system, scheduling all work on job card system.  Maintain the computerized maintenance program. Replenish stores as necessary.\n \nPositions working conditions:\nNormal working hours, with flexibility within reason when high demand dictates otherwise\nAdministrative duties as determined by direct senior\nNoisy and fast paced environment\n \nQualification Requirements   \nQualifications & Experience\nGrade 12 with strong numerical and MS Office basic skill level\nArtisan Qualification is advantageous.\nStores, planned maintenance qualifications will receive priority\n \nExperience Requirements    \nExperience: \n3-5 Years\u2019 experience in planned Maintenance systems\nKnowledge of Milling equipment/parts is advantageous\nClear understanding of maintenance in factory environments\nVehicle license is mandatory\n \nCompetencies (knowledge, skills and attributes):\nAttention to detail\nGood Planning and Organizing skills\nFollowing Instructions and Procedures\nRelating and Networking\nDelivering Results and Meeting Customer Expectations.\nKnowledge of Planned, predictive, corrective maintenance principles is required\nKnowledge of HSE, FMCG, FSSC is essential\nGood communication skills are required\nTeamwork in a fast pace continuous process\nMust be able to work independently within the team dynamic\nAdministrative task orientation\nAccuracy, quick learner\nTime management skills\nInnovation / Continuous Improvement\nAccountability and responsibility to planned maintenance\nSense of urgency/ Results orientated\nRespect\n \nKey Outputs\nResponsibilities:\nMaintenance admin tasks related to Maintenance HSE, FSSC and reporting\nPlan and schedule periodic maintenance on maintenance system\nPlan purchasing of specific parts\nClose out all job cards on the system\nProvide data for decision making from maintenance system\nAssist value chain clerk with production related task\n \n \nPolicy\nPlease note that it is company policy to promote from within wherever possible, hence internal applicants will be given priority. We recruit and appoint in line with our Employment Equity Goals and objectives.\n \nPLEASE APPLY HERE",
                "DEPOT MANAGER\n \nDetails\nClosing Date: 2023/10/02\nReference Number: PRE230928-3\nJob Title: Depot Manager\nDepartment: Depot\nSite: 672 \u2013 BR: Queenstown Depot\nJob Type Classification: Permanent\nLocation \u2013 Country: South Africa\nLocation - Town / City: Queenstown\nLocation \u2013 Province: Eastern Cape\n \nJob Description\nTo ensure the delivery of Premier products in time and in full every day. Incumbent will also be responsible for overseeing the co-ordination of all the functions on site including staff management and client liaison. Ensure growth of bread sales in the informal market and that delivery of bread is made on time and in full. To manage a depot sales teams\u2019 performance to grow profitable sales for their area in line with site sales strategic plans and targets.\n \nQualification Requirements\nMatric\nRelevant Diploma / Degree in Business\nComputer literacy \u2013 Excel, MS Word\n \nExperience Requirements\n3 \u2013 5 years\u2019 experience in a managerial position or similar\n \nKey Outputs   \nCreate and maintain brand awareness into minds and hearts:\nVisibility\nLoyalty\nConsistency\nTo become a reliable distributor\n \nAsset management and Housekeeping:\nEfficient crate control\nVehicle abuse\nMaintain truck image\n \nDevelop the supply chain:\nDeliver at the right cost\nPlan execution of orders\nCustomer Relationship Management\nMaximize customer service levels\nGet the right products to customers on time, in full every day\nStock management\nReports and Administration\nSecurity Control\nProcess Management\nStaff Management and Development\nLabour management/ Industrial Relations\nIncreased sales volumes\nIncreased Customer satisfaction\nTo develop and propose site volume targets and plans to the site and regional manager in line with the national plans and targets.\nTo implement, monitor, report, and review sales delivery against agreed targets (volume and margin)\nTo implement, monitor and report on the roll out of corporate initiatives such as route viability, DRM, Pricing etc. through relevant cross functional Invocom and reports\nTo manage the performance of direct reports through preparation and facilitation of weekly site sales team Invocom.\nTo support compliance to internal process, practice and SOPs via monthly and quarterly auditing, collation and presentation of sales pack info to the relevant managers.\nTo schedule and coordinate the on-site sales pack audit and present findings to the regional sales manager and relevant bakery/depot managers in order to agree corrective action and continuous improvement\nTo manage and motivate high performance teams through the decisive management of non- performance and quick recognition of good performance in line with company process and procedures and provide training, coaching and mentoring as needed\nTo manage third party suppliers or outsourced service providers to ensure good execution and customer services to our customers.\n \n \nPolicy\nPlease note that it is company policy to promote from within wherever possible, hence internal applicants will be given priority. We recruit and appoint in line with our Employment Equity Goals and objectives.\n \nPLEASE APPLY HERE"
