                " \n \n \n \nMANAGEMENT ACCOUNTANT\nListing reference: click_014413\nListing status: Online\nApply by: 18 October 2023\n \nPosition summary\nIndustry: Wholesale & Retail Trade\nJob category: Other Accounting, Auditing\nLocation: Cape Town\nContract: Permanent\nEE position: Yes\n \nIntroduction\nWe are looking to recruit a Management Accountant to work within the Group Accounts Payable department of The Clicks Group. The role will be based at Clicks Head Office in Cape Town and will report to the Accounts Payable Manager.\n \nJob description\nJob Purpose:\nTo ensure accurate payments are processed to suppliers in accordance with agreed contractual terms; and provide accurate, timeous and relevant financial information to facilitate decision-making.\n \nJob Objectives:\nManage the reporting and payment processes.\nSupport the Accounts Payable Manager in overseeing the efficiency and effectiveness of the accounts payable function.\nTo ensure that financial transactions are processed accurately and on time.\nTo lead the month end closing and internal and external auditing processes.\nTo enforce standards of compliance for accounts payable processes.\nTo investigate and resolve accounts payable issues as required.\nTo ensure general ledger and vendor accounts are reconciled and reconciling differences are resolved within the required timelines, thereby minimising the exposure to the Group.\nTo ensure all documentation processed complies with the relevant VAT legislation.\nTo accurately plan and forecast supplier payments on a monthly and annual basis to facilitate forecasting of cash resources required.\nTo create and maintain accounts payable processes and procedures.\nTo build strong relationships with suppliers and colleagues.\nTo provide coaching and mentoring to staff and ensure that they are adequately trained to perform their functions within the Accounts Payable Department.\nMaintenance of terms and conditions of internal and external service level agreements to ensure that these are met consistently.\n \nMinimum requirements\nQualifications and Experience:\nB.Com Accounting Degree with Major Subjects Accounting 3 (essential).\nB.Com Honours in Related Subjects (desirable).\n1 to 3 Years Accountant with Accounts Payable Management experience (essential).\nGeneral retail experience (essential).\n \nSkills, Abilities and Job Related Knowledge:\nExposure to retail operations and stock receipting processes.\nKnowledge of Group Accounting Methodology.\nKnowledge of Accounts Payable Accounting.\nKnowledge of Staff Development Principles.\nKnowledge of Performance Management Principles.\nCommunication and report writing skills.\nProblem solving skills.\nManagement skills.\nAnalysing and diagnosing skills.\nNegotiation and interpersonal skills.\nComputer literacy.\n \nEssential Competencies:\nDeciding and Initiating Action.\nLeading and Supervising.\nAdhering to Principles and Values.\nAnalysing.\nPlanning and Organising.\nDelivering Results and Meeting Customer Expectations.\nFollowing Instructions and Procedures.\nEntrepreneurial and Commercial Thinking.\n \nAPPLY\n \n \n \n ",
