                " \n \nPERSONAL TRAINER\nListing reference: vaclb_001255\nListing status: Online\nApply by: 31 October 2023\n \nPosition summary\nIndustry: Health & Fitness\nJob category: Sports and Fitness\nLocation: Gauteng\nContract: Permanent\nRemuneration: Market Related\nEE position: No\nIntroduction\nYour Purpose... As a personal trainer for Virgin Active, you will have the opportunity to operate your own business, by making use of our facilities and activities on the floor. You will manage your client base and offer personal training programmes to our members.\n \nJob description\nKey Responsibilities of the Job:\nDesigning safe and effective exercise programs for your client base\nProviding high levels of customer service to personal training clients and all Virgin Active members\nBuilding a sustainable personal training client base by continually adding new clients and retaining existing clients\nCompleting and maintaining accurate personal training client records stored in the designated club areas\nMaintaining appropriate professional boundaries\nRespond and act in the case of club emergencies\nParticipate in all club related activities as required\nHelping create a fun atmosphere within the fitness areas\nFollow all Personal Training guidelines and standards as set by Virgin Active\nEnsure that all certificate is valid and up to date according to industry standards\n \nMinimum Requirements:\nMatric qualification\nA recognized Personal Training qualification\n1- 2 years\u2019 experience within personal training\nA current First Aid, CPR and AED certification\nAn outgoing and friendly personality coupled with good communication skills\nSelf-motivated to achieve set income targets\nSelf-disciplined to build and maintain a client base\n \nPLEASE APPLY HERE\n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \nSWIM INSTRUCTOR\nListing reference: vaclb_001278\nListing status: Online\nApply by: 15 October 2023\n \nPosition summary\nIndustry: Health & Fitness\nJob category: Sports and Fitness\nLocation: Umhlanga\nContract: Permanent\nRemuneration: Market Related\nEE position: No\n \nIntroduction\nYour Purpose... \u2022 To inspire people to live an active life. \u2022 To live and role-model our Values of Always learning, always improving; Inspiring People; Have fun; and Do the right thing; and to bring to life our People Promise of We are one team and want our people to always feel they can be themselves. We work hard and we dream big. \u2022 To be responsible for teaching scheduled swim lessons for children. \u2022 To be responsible for ensuring that all poolside activities are promoted and run effectively. \u2022 To provide a supportive customer experience role, providing personal attention and care to all customers. \u2022 Create and develop creative and innovative classes following the Virgin Active and STA swim criteria that also supports the Virgin Active brand. \u2022 To ensure all juniors as assessed regular, retained, and moved through our programme. \u2022 Always be punctual, reliable and adhere to the high standards of organisation required by the company. \u2022 Attend training courses which will enable you to carry out your role successfully and to assist with your future career progression. \u2022 To ensure a safe environment is kept at all times for the juniors and that you immediately report anything you see to the Swim Manager or the MOD as soon as possible.\n \nJob description\nYour Duties and Responsibilities...\nKeep abreast of information on all club facilities, programmes, social events, customer suggestions in order to ensure you are fully aware of what is going on across the club and can be an important link between members and all other departments.\nTo be responsible for ensuring any concerns you have regarding Safeguarding Children & Vulnerable adults are reported to your Swim Manager.\nTo be involved with the Swim Manager to drive occupancy in the department through a world class timetable offering.\nTo assist the Swim Manager to drive the department to achieve set targets, meet objectives and be commercially successful.\nWorking with the Swim Manager to drive retention and Net Growth.\nHave knowledge of and Promote the Family activities products within the club.\nBe proactive, use your initiative and take ownership of situations.\nMaintain a positive, productive working relationship with all other colleagues. Help to create an environment where all colleagues enjoy themselves whilst at work and make a real contribution to the success of the club and business as a whole.\nOversee the smooth running of classes taking place in the pool area, ensuring the classes you teach consistently meet the Virgin Active world class standards.\nEnsure that all scheduled classes take place and never cancelled, unless in extenuating circumstances.\nMonitor class attendance by completing class registers accurately.\nEnsure good relations with all class participants.\nBe fully involved in the creation of a fun, lively and creative atmosphere for all members. Take part in activities, programs and events in the Club which are engaging, generate revenue and promote retention.\nListen and respond positively to any member concerns and pass on any necessary information and observations to the Swim Manager who will give feedback within 48 hours of receipt.\nEnsure that the pool area is safe at all times (for example considering temperature, equipment, obstacles, number of participants etc.) and if necessary, reinforce pool regulations with members in order to further maintain their own and others\u2019 safety.\nBe fully aware of all emergency and evacuation procedures and take part in regular training to maintain up to date knowledge of these procedures.\nHave a thorough understanding of the Virgin Active brand standards and be able to interpret and deliver them on a daily basis, ensuring the pool areas and equipment are maintained and presented as laid out in the brand standards.\nBe aware of the importance of membership sales and continually aim to maximise all sales opportunities within the club.\nBe aware of the importance of member retention and understand your role in influencing members who are considering leaving the club to stay.\nBe aware of the importance of member satisfaction on club performance, proactively monitor all sources of member feedback and seek to identify opportunities to improve member engagement and satisfaction wherever possible.\n \nMinimum requirements\nOur Minimum Requirements...\n \nWe can\u2019t live without\u2026\nA passion and awareness for Swimming and legal requirements.\nSwim South Africa/STA Full Swim Instructor qualification (or recognised equivalent).\nHas great passion and pride in their own work.\nAbility to work from instruction effectively and safely with minimal supervision.\nA flexible attitude to working patterns.\nDemonstration of the Virgin Active Values.\nDrive, passion, and commitment to work within a fast-paced business.\nStrong interpersonal abilities and someone who is approachable to members and other employees at all times - it is vital that employees in this role have a genuine interest in wanting to resolve members\u2019 queries and deliver an experience above and beyond our customers\u2019 expectations.\nExcellent Communication Skills.\nA flexible attitude to working patterns with ability to work evenings, weekends and public holidays as required.\nClear Police Clearance Check (prior to commencing).\n \nPLEASE APPLY HERE\n \n \n \n ",
