                " \n \n \n \nEXERCISE EXPERIENCE MANAGER\nListing reference: vaclb_001297\nListing status: Online\nApply by: 8 October 2023\n \nPosition summary\nIndustry: Health & Fitness\nJob category: Sports and Fitness\nLocation: Pietermaritzburg\nContract: Permanent\nRemuneration: Market Related\nEE position: No\nIntroduction\nCascades Virgin Active - Your Purpose... To Inspire people to live active lives. Virgin Active is looking for an Exercise Experience Manager to make exercise irresistible for our members, using all Exercise-related programmes as a tool to ensure, consistent value-add and top-class member experiences, resulting in repeat member visits and retention.\n \nJob description\nYour Duties and Responsibilities...\nTo at all times do your bit towards achieving our purpose to Inspire people to live an active life, this is achieved by believing and living our values through all we do, always innovating, inspiring people, have fun and do the right thing.\nProvide a welcoming environment to all new members via a comprehensive induction to the club facility, as well as consistently irresistible exercise experiences. Promoting and supporting this via the 30-day Kickstart ancillary strategy\nAttract, recruit and retain a team of \u2018Rockstar\u2019 Fitness Instructors & Group Exercise Instructors in line with the club FTE & budget\nComplete detailed company induction with Fitness, Group Exercise Instructors & independent contractors\nProvide the Club Exercise Team with the opportunity to maximize their personal and professional development through regular training, coaching and feedback\nDevelop optimum staffing schedules to ensure adequate floor coverage\nActively promote all relevant ancillary offerings to both new and existing members, prioritizing an irresistible member experience\nImplement and effectively deliver on all exercise-related strategies in the club\nInvest in your own self-development through formal training, continued education and on-the-job learning opportunities\nMaximize the member experience and engagement through the delivery of small group exercise classes and member events\nExpand and optimize the group exercise offering and timetable in your club\nEnsure daily capturing of attendance, analyzing class performance and report on success in your club (or identify gaps and action plans to speedily address any under-performance to speedily attain required standards)\nEnsure that all group exercise locations are in excellent condition regarding sound systems and all other equipment\nDrive continued education (CEC\u2019s) with all staff, independent contractors and the Group Exercise Instructor base of your club and ensure 100% CEC requirement is met\nMaximize member engagement through Group Exercise in the facility with Red Hot events, such as, FITFEST & DJ evenings, etc.\nIncrease Mobile app engagement and GEX bookings in your club\nBuild an excellent Group Exercise instructor community in your club\nUtilize the GEX & PT Mentors to assess and continually support the improvement and development of the current group exercise instructor and Personal training base in line with Virgin Active brand standards\nContinuously seek out opportunities to increase and improve on Group Exercise offerings regarding club space\nEnsure effective, on brand in-club marketing of all exercise aspects\nIntroduce, drive and optimize a GEX invitation system in your club\nMake use of company approved marketing and campaign tools to promote Personal Training and Group Exercise to your members\nEnsure a safe floor environment via the implementation, and adherence to all standardized and relevant Health and Safety requirements, Ops Standards and Brilliant Basics\n \nMinimum requirements\nOur Minimum Requirements...\n \nWe can\u2019t live without\u2026\nMatric qualification\nA recognized Fitness Qualification\nA recognized Group Exercise Qualification\nA minimum of 2 years\u2019 experience within the Fitness.\nA minimum of 1 years\u2019 experience in managing people / teams\nExceptional people leadership skills\nHigh energy levels\nA strong team player\nExcellent interpersonal skills with the ability to build strong relationships\nExperience in teaching a variety of Group Exercise classes\n \nWe\u2019d love you to have\u2026\nExperience in teaching small group classes\nThe ability to coach and mentor people\nExcellent facilitation and presentation skills\nEvent organizing and coordinating skills\nMarketing & social media skills\n \nWe\u2019d like you to have\u2026\nHealth Club experience\nInfluencing skills\n \nPLEASE APPLY HERE\n \n \n \n \n ",
